    "title": "Principal Radiologist at Medtronic India",
    "description": "Medtronic India, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Radiologist for our Agra operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout Medtronic India:\nMedtronic India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Referral bonus program\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Medtronic India!",
